<P>REMARKS ON THE PROPOSED PLAN OF AN EMISSION OF PAPER, AND ON THE MEANS OF EFFECTING IT, ADDRESSED TO THE CITIZENS OF MARYLAND, BY ARISTIDES.</P>
<Q><P>When in a popular Government there is a Su&s;pen&s;ion of the Laws, as this can proceed only from the Corruption of the Re|public, the State is certainly undone.</P>
<BIBL><HI>MONTESQ. SP. of LAWS, b. 3, ch. 3.</HI></BIBL></Q>
<P>ANNAPOLIS: PRINTED BY FREDERICK GREEN.</P>
</DIV1>
